==English==

===Etymology===
*From Latin, ascribere: ''ad'' to, +''scribere'' write 

===Transitive Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|ascrib|e}}

# To attribute, impute, or refer, as to a cause.
# To ascribe, as death to a poison.
# To ascribe an effect to the right cause.
# To ascribe such a book to such an author.

